pygame.pixelcopy
pygame module for general pixel array copying

The pygame.pixelcopy module contains methods for copying between surfaces
and objects exporting an array structure interface.

New in pygame 1.9.2.
<SECTION>


surface_to_array
copy surface pixels to an array object
pygame.pixelcopy.surface_to_array(array, surface, kind='P', opaque=255, clear=0): return None

Copy a surface to an array object.
<END>


array_to_surface
copy an array object to a surface
pygame.pixelcopy.array_to_surface(<surface>, <array>): returns None

Copy an array to a surface.
<END>


map_array
copy an array to another array, using surface format
pygame.pixelcopy.map_array(<array>, <array>, <surface>): return None

Map an array of color element values - (w, h, ..., 3) - to an array of pixels -
(w, h) according to the format of <surface>.
<END>


make_surface
Copy an array to a new surface
pygame.surfarray.make_surface(array): return Surface

Create a new Surface that best resembles the data and format on the
array. The array can be 2D or 3D with any sized integer values.
<END>
<END>

